#
# # vr4_2_native_call
#
# VR.4.2 — leaf-bodied helper goes through the native ABI
#
# ## Notes
#
# fz-cps.1.12: load.i64 in square is now Term::Return's indirect-call
# (load cont+8) per docs/cps-in-clif.md §2.1.
#
# fz-ul4.27.6.2 — `square` qualifies for the typed-arity native ABI:
#   * non-parking (no Receive / closures),
#   * never used as a continuation,
#   * not main,
#   * body-leaf (only Term::Return — no Call / TailCall / CallClosure),
#   * directly called via Term::Call from main.
# So it's declared with the `Tail` calling convention as
# `(i64, i64) -> i64`, runs synchronously inside main's call site, and
# returns its result via register. No `fz_alloc_frame` for the callee
# frame, no entry-frame slot loads inside the body.
#
# main still goes through the uniform ABI (excluded from native — main
# is the trampoline's entry point). main's call site for `square` does
# allocate the continuation frame (cont still rides uniform ABI in
# .6.2.x; native cont invocation is .6.3) and then writes the tagged
# native return into cont slot 1 before handing the cont frame ptr to
# the trampoline. The matrix runs jit / interp / aot to prove the
# behavior matches across the three paths.
fn square(x) do
  x * x
end

fn main() do
  dbg(square(7))
end
